==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*sagjanan''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[sega]], Old Saxon [[seggian]] (Dutch [[zeggen]]), Old High German [[sagen|sagēn]] (German [[sagen]]), Old Norse [[segja]] (Swedish [[säga]]).

